import React, { useState } from 'react'; import './VehicleOrderForm.css'; interface VehicleOrderFormData { model: string; year: number; country: string; supplier: string; vehicleCost: number; currency: 'USD' | 'JPY' | 'EUR' | 'GBP'; expectedDelivery: string; notes: string; expenses: { fuel: number; duty: number; driverCharge: number; clearanceCharge: number; demurrage: number; tax: number; customExpenses: { [key: string]: number }; }; paymentMethod: string; } interface VehicleOrderFormProps { onSubmit: (data: VehicleOrderFormData) => void; onCancel: () => void; initialData?: VehicleOrderFormData; isEditing?: boolean; } const VehicleOrderForm: React.FC = ({ onSubmit, onCancel, initialData, isEditing }) => { const [formData, setFormData] = useState( initialData || { model: '', year: new Date().getFullYear(), country: 'Japan', supplier: '', vehicleCost: 0, currency: 'USD', expectedDelivery: '', notes: '', expenses: { fuel: 0, duty: 0, driverCharge: 0, clearanceCharge: 0, demurrage: 0, tax: 0, customExpenses: {}, }, paymentMethod: 'Bank Transfer', } ); const handleInputChange = (e: React.ChangeEvent) => { const { name, value } = e.target; if (name.startsWith('expenses.')) { const expenseKey = name.split('.')[1] as keyof typeof formData.expenses; setFormData(prev => ({ ...prev, expenses: { ...prev.expenses, [expenseKey]: parseFloat(value) || 0 } })); } else { setFormData(prev => ({ ...prev, [name]: name === 'year' || name === 'vehicleCost' ? parseFloat(value) || 0 : value })); } }; const handleSubmit = (e: React.FormEvent) => { e.preventDefault(); onSubmit(formData); }; const getTotalCost = () => { const expenseTotal = Object.values(formData.expenses).reduce((sum, val) => sum + val, 0); return formData.vehicleCost + expenseTotal; }; return (
